The paper proposes a method for efficient query-specific network construction using data cube organization and reinforcement learning. This involves dealing with real-world massive networks with complex attributes, which suggests a focus on database-related topics (cs.DB). The use of reinforcement learning also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions downstream tasks, which could fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI) or systems and control (cs.SY).
